  "input": "Rehospitalization form\nThe child Maabed Mouad aged 12, originally from and residing in Algiers, from a 03rd degree consanguineous couple, followed since the age of 08, for a combined syndromic DIP type Ataxia telangectasia. Admitted today 12/15/2025 for immunoglobulin treatment No. 04. HISTORY:\nFamily:\n- Father: 41 years old; BES. - Mother: 33 years old, G8P04A03M01\n- 3rd degree consanguinity. - Siblings:\nOur Sick\nBoy aged 10, with a history of a single kidney not investigated, RSP followed by a private pediatrician placed on GH since the age of 3 and for 6 months. Boy aged 08 in BES\nBoy died at the age of 2 months (Cantrell Pentalogy)\nBoy aged 13 months with a history of hospitalization for 10 days for undocumented DR + adrenal insufficiency\nPersonal:\nPhysiological:\n-Pregnancy: well monitored. -Delivery: by VB at term. - Apgar good at birth. 9/10\n-Birth weight: 03 kg\n- Calm neonatal period\n-Exclusive breastfeeding for up to one month then artificial breastfeeding. -Dietary diversification: 06 months. - vitamin D received at 1 month. - Vaccination: done up to 6 years old\nPathological:\n-Delay in psychomotor acquisitions\n-Repeated ear infections since the age of 3\n-Recurrent allergic rhinitis\n-Seizures since the age of 4\nHistory of illness:\nMain diagnosis: Syndromic combined PID type Ataxia telangiectasia. Diagnostic elements:\nAnamnestic: Concept of 3rd degree consanguinity\nConcept of death among siblings at a young age\nConcept of recurrent respiratory infections\nClinical: Static and kinetic ataxia\nBilateral telangiectasia\nParaclinical: Assessment of immunodeficiency done on 05/22/2025: in favor of ataxia telangiectasia syndrome (Louis Bar syndrome)\nAssociated diagnosis: Pulmonary hamartochondroma/EPILEPSY/Right tympanic perforation\nDate of diagnosis: 2021\nAge of diagnosis: 08 years. Hospitalization history:\nAutoimmunity assessment: 11/30/2025 Antinuclear Antibody Screening: Negative\nGastric tube result: negative direct examination and negative culture\nAlpha fetoprotein 09/11/2025: 360.4 iu/mL\nProcessing in progress\nItraconazole 5mg/kg/day\nBactrim: 25mg/kg/day\nKepam: 220 mg *2/day\nTherapeutic compliance: Good\nIntermediate history:\nConsultation: yes (Parnet Hospital)\nOn the respiratory level: 07/12/2025 Wet cough\nOn the digestive level: 11/29/2025 Acute gastroenteritis, treated with: ORS, Smecta, Augmentin (for 10 days)\nOn the oral level: 12/12/2025 Dental abscess treated with flagyl + clamoxyl\nNeurologically: 11/12/2025 and 12/12/2025 2 convulsive attacks lasting 2 min made up of fixed gaze and tonic seizure of the upper limbs\nOn the genital level: Intervention for cryptorchidism cancelled. CLINICAL EXAMINATION UPON ADMISSION: Date: 15/12/2025\nAnthropometric measurements:\nWeight: 19 kg (-3.90 DS). Underweight\nSize: 123CM (-3.29 DS). Marked stature delay\nBMI: 13.8% (-2.9)\nGeneral condition preserved, afebrile: T: 36.6° C,\nSkin exam:\nPresence of cutaneous xerosis with slight white scales around the mouth\nTelangiectasia in the right cheek\nDry dandruff on the hair\nPleuropulmonary examination:\nWet cough with slightly greenish sputum,\nEupneic, Fr: 20c/min, SpO2: 98% under ambient air\nNo respiratory distress\nLung auscultation: snoring rales with bronchial congestion\nNo signs of respiratory failure\nCardiovascular examination: HR: 89 b/min, CRT < 3 sec, Auscultation: B1, B2 audible properties, absence of added noises\nAbdominopelvic examination: Soft abdomen, no organomegaly, free hernial orifices, preserved transit\nOphthalmological examination: Bilateral telangiectasia, rotatory nystagmus\nENT: no otorrhea\nExamination of genitals: male morphotype, no ADS, TANNER stage 1, bilateral cryptorchidism\nOsteoarticular examination:\nSpine deformity,\nEquinus foot deformity\nNeurological examination:\nInability to walk (drunken walking): Kinetic ataxia\nImpossibility of standing without support: Static ataxia\nWord: Bradylalia, cerebellar dysarthria\nReview of other devices: Is unremarkable\nPARACLINICAL ASSESSMENT UPON ADMISSION: 15/12/25\nCBC: GB: 4600 elements, PNN: 2900 element/mm lymphocytes: 1000 elements/mm\nHB: 10.9g/dl; MCV: 82.1 fl;\nCCMH: 34.8 Discrete normocytic normochromic anemia\nPLQ: 327,000 el/mm 3. CRP: Between 12 and 24 mg/l\nPCT: 0.05 ng/ml\nPT: 14.3sec TP: 81.5% TCK: 34 sec Fibrinogen: 3.57 g/l\nASAT: 30.9U/l ALT: 21.6 U/L gGt: 25.15 U/l PAL: 261.8 U/l\nWhat to do:\n-Hospitalization\n-Condition, peripheral venous route\n- ECBC with mycological and parasitological study + antibiogram launched\n-Launched a complete assessment\n- Immunoglobulin treatment at 0.8 g/kg or 15g over 4 hours 30 min\n-Education of the mother for respiratory physiotherapy\nDuring the treatment: The immunoglobulin treatment passed without incident,\nThe child is discharged on 12/16/2025 with a check-up appointment: 01/18/2026. CONCLUSION:\nThe child Maabed Mouad aged 12, originally from and residing in Algiers, from a 3rd degree consanguineous couple, followed for a syndromic combined DIP type Ataxia telangiectasia, Admitted to our level for his treatment of immunoglobulin No. 04. To collect / To do:\nDischarge the patient with: Clamoxyl tab 01g every 8 hours (PDT 10 days) + Zomax tab 500mg/day (PDT 5 days)\nRetrieval of ECBC results + stool coproparasitology\nPatient scheduled for tooth extraction on 16/12/2025\nRecover the level of residual IgG during the next treatment\nAppointment for the 5th Immunoglobulin treatment on 01/18/2026\nDepartment resident: Dr Djoudi Department assistant: Dr Doukar",
